<article class="about-page">

  <div class="about-hero">
    <span class="about-tagline">The story</span>
    <h1>Real food from<br><em>a real kitchen.</em></h1>
    <p class="about-intro">
      Immy's Cafe started when we canceled our Beehive Meals subscription and realized
      we could make better food for less money with a freezer, a slow cooker, and
      about 30 minutes on a Sunday.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="about-body">

    <section class="about-section">
      <h2>Who is Immy?</h2>
      <p>
        Immy is Imogen — the reason we started cooking more intentionally in the first place.
        This site is named for her.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="about-section">
      <h2>Why freezer meals?</h2>
      <p>
        Meal kit services are convenient until you do the math. We were paying a lot for
        convenience we could replicate ourselves. A gallon freezer bag, a slow cooker,
        and 10 minutes of prep is all it takes. Come home, dump it in, eat well.
      </p>
      <p>
        Every recipe on this site is one we actually cook. If it didn't make the rotation,
        it doesn't get posted.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="about-section">
      <h2>How the recipes work</h2>
      <p>
        Each recipe is designed to go from freezer bag straight into a slow cooker —
        no thawing required. Prep time is real (usually under 15 minutes).
        The ingredients are things you can actually find at a normal grocery store.
      </p>
      <p>
        Every recipe page includes a full ingredient list formatted so you can import it
        directly into Samsung Food and push to Walmart or Instacart for checkout.
        That's the whole system.
      </p>
    </section>

